<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-11-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-11-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="794" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d794">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Phelps</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 325.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-11-05"><hi rend="italic">November 5,
                                1891</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Adverting to my No. 317, of the 28th
                            ultimo, confirmatory of my telegram to you of the 26th of the same month
                            in relation to the reported resignation of the president of the
                            municipal council of Samoa, I herewith inclose copy of the Department’s
                            note of the 28th ultimo to the minister of Great Britain at this
                            capital, and of his reply of the 31st of the same month upon the
                            subject.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>